<!-- TL;DR -->
<div class="tldr">
<h4><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-20"><use href="#pg-info"></use></svg> If you only have 30 seconds</h4>
<p>Get <b>traditional Thai massage</b> if you want deep, energising work on tight muscles and stiff joints — it's dry, fully clothed, uses stretching and pressure, and runs about <b>฿200–350 an hour</b> in Pattaya. Get <b>oil (aromatherapy) massage</b> if you want to relax and unwind — it's gentle, uses warm oil on bare skin, and runs about <b>฿300–500 an hour</b>. Rule of thumb: <b>Thai for "fix my body", oil for "calm my mind."</b> If you're sunburnt, hungover or just want to switch off, choose oil; if your back and shoulders are knotted, choose Thai.</p>
</div>
</div>
