ost family-friendly thing to do at night."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Tiffany's &amp; Alcazar cabaret", "description": "Slick hour-long transgender cabaret shows, ฿800–1,200, all ages. Pattaya's signature evening spectacle."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Walking Street &amp; Bali Hai", "description": "The famous neon bar strip from ~7pm, plus a sea view at Bali Hai Pier. Worth one stroll as spectacle; adults-only in spirit."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Rooftop bars with a view", "description": "Horizon at the Hilton and other hotel rooftops, ฿250–450 cocktails, best at sunset. The best couples' opener."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 5, "name": "Koh Larn sunset ferry", "description": "Time the last ~6pm ferry (฿30) to catch sunset over the water — Pattaya's best free show."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 6, "name": "Family-friendly nights", "description": "Frost Magical Ice of Siam and Pattaya Park Tower (฿300–500), plus the cabaret and night markets — easy bar-free evenings for kids."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 7, "name": "Sanctuary of Truth at dusk", "description": "The floodlit all-teak landmark (~฿500), best in the early evening. Calm, photogenic and couple-friendly."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 8, "name": "Beach Road night stroll", "description": "A free, breezy walk along the bay with food carts and city lights. Good for everyone."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 9, "name": "Live-music &amp; jazz bars", "description": "Relaxed bars around Soi Buakhao, ฿80–200 drinks. A laid-back alternative to the go-go strips."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 10, "name": "Late-night street eats", "description": "24-hour noodle and rice stalls (Soi Honey area), ฿50–120 — the night owl's reward."}]}, {"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": [{"@type": "Question", "name": "What are the best things to do in Pattaya at night that aren't bars?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "The best non-bar nights are a night market (Lan Po in Naklua or Thepprasit, with ฿40–80 street food), a cabaret show at Tiffany's or Alcazar (฿800–1,200), the Sanctuary of Truth at dusk (around ฿500), a Koh Larn sunset ferry (฿30) and a rooftop-bar view. All are easy to reach by ฿10–30 songthaew."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Is Pattaya at night family-friendly?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, far more than its reputation suggests. The Tiffany's and Alcazar cabaret shows are tasteful and fine for all ages, the night markets are great for kids, and Frost Magical Ice of Siam plus the Pattaya Park Tower (฿300–500) make easy family evenings. Just keep children away from the Walking Street go-go strip."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "How much does a night out in Pattaya cost?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "A budget night of a market dinner and a Koh Larn sunset ferry runs ฿300–500 per person. A classic night with a cabaret ticket, dinner and a rooftop cocktail is around ฿1,000–1,500. A big night with rooftop drinks, a sit-down dinner and a bar crawl can top ฿2,500. Songthaews home cost ฿10–30."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "What time do things in Pattaya start at night?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Night markets open around 5pm and run to 11pm. Cabaret shows run at roughly 6pm, 7:30pm and 9pm. Walking Street closes to traffic and gets going from about 7pm. The Sanctuary of Truth and Koh Larn ferries are late-afternoon-into-sunset (last entry/ferry around 5–6:30pm), so plan those earlier."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Is it safe to walk around Pattaya at night?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Generally yes — Beach Road, Central Pattaya and the markets are busy and safe for couples, families and solo travellers. Stick to lit, busy areas, ignore touts offering \"free\" bars or shows, agree taxi and jet-ski prices in advance, and use metered Grab or so