<img alt="Pattaya best tours – 30 BestThings to Doin Pattaya" fetchpriority="high" height="506" loading="eager" src="../Pattaya-Tum-Gorseller-Resized/pattaya-best-tours.webp" width="1100"/>
<figcaption class="cap"><span class="lead"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-16"><use href="#pg-pin"></use></svg> Pattaya packs islands, temples, shows and beaches into one compact bay</span><span class="credit">Go To Pattaya</span></figcaption>
</figure>
<!-- TL;DR -->
<div class="tldr">
<h4><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-20"><use href="#pg-info"></use></svg> If you only have 30 seconds</h4>
<p><b>Short on time?</b> The four things almost everyone should do in Pattaya: a day trip to <b>Koh Larn (Coral Island)</b> — ฿30 ferry, 45 min from <b>Bali Hai Pier</b>; the all-teak <b>Sanctuary of Truth</b> in Naklua (<b>฿500</b>); a <b>cabaret show</b> at Tiffany's or Alcazar (<b>฿800–1,200</b>, ~75 min, family-friendly); and a slow morning on <b>Jomtien</b> or <b>Wong Amat Beach</b>. Bring cash, start early, and book islands and water parks for a weekday to dodge the crowds.</p>
</div>
</div>
<!-- LAYOUT -->
<div class="art-layout">
<article class="art-body">
<!-- MOBILE STICKY TOC -->
<div class="mtoc">
