<!-- HERO -->
<figure class="art-hero"><img alt="Pattaya night clubs 2 – Tiffany Show Pattaya: Tickets, Times and Is It Worth It?" fetchpriority="high" height="506" loading="eager" src="../Pattaya-Tum-Gorseller-Resized/pattaya-night-clubs-2.webp" width="1100"/>
      <figcaption class="cap"><span class="lead"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-16"><use href="#pg-pin"></use></svg> Tiffany's Show — Pattaya's original cabaret, running on Second Road since 1974</span><span class="credit">Go To Pattaya</span></figcaption></figure>
<!-- TL;DR -->
<div class="tldr">
<h4><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-20"><use href="#pg-info"></use></svg> If you only have 30 seconds</h4>
<p><b>Worth it?</b> Yes, for the spectacle and the value. The <b>Tiffany Show Pattaya</b> is the city's original ladyboy cabaret (running since <b>1974</b> on <b>Second Road</b>): ~75 minutes of dazzling costumes, lip-sync and cultural numbers, and it's genuinely <b>family-friendly</b> (no nudity). Tickets run <b>฿800–1,200</b> by tier. Show times are typically <b>~18:00, 19:30 and 21:00</b> — confirm current times when you book. Its rival <b>Alcazar</b> is a few minutes away and just as polished; pick by show time and seat price.</p>
</div>
</div>
